FBIS4-1469 "drafr083_b_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-083 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia Armed Abductors Release Sudanese Ambassador Armed Abductors Release Sudanese Ambassador EA2704172994 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in Arabic 1300 GMT 27 Apr 94 EA2704172994 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] The Sudanese ambassador to Somalia, 'Abd-al-Baqi Muhammad Hasan Ahmad, who was abducted on 19 April by an armed group belonging to the Hawadle clan, was released today in Mogadishu. Reports confirmed that the ambassador was in good health. The ambassador, in a statement to a SUDAN NEWS AGENCY correspondent, expressed his thanks and appreciation to all those concerned with his case throughout his abduction. He stated that he would soon leave Mogadishu for Khartoum. Sudan's ambassador to Somalia is the only Arab ambassador who has been present in Mogadishu throughout the developments in Somalia.
